metadata.name: The Goddess of Chaos
metadata.description: The image of this Goddess was inspired by the God named Chaos from ancient Greek mythology, that simbolizing the "creatio ex nihilo" (created from nothing) and this God is the progenitor of all other gods and the entire Cosmos. –ês well as one of the "Highest Gods" of the Warhammer universe, whose name Tzeentch, that have many names like "Architect of Fate", "Master of Destiny", "Changer of the Ways" and symbolizing the desire for change, no matter change of what exactly: Galaxies, Planets, Space, Time or Human Destinies.
